This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to optimize the configuration of modular software systems. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves machine learning techniques. The paper also mentions the use of metareasoning, which is a subfield of AI concerned with reasoning about reasoning, further supporting the cs.AI category. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the application of these techniques in various areas such as transportation, healthcare, and industrial automation, which could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
